Beijing Sets Up Deng Thought Research Institute
BEIJING , February 27 ( Xinhua ) -- The establishment of the Beijing Deng Xiaoping Thought Research Institute was announced here today at the Great Hall of the People .
Set up on the occasion of the first anniversary of the death of senior leader Deng , the institute aims to promote study and research into Deng 's thought in the spheres of politics , economy , culture , education , science and technology , and military and diplomatic affairs , with an eye to applying his ideas in the course of building a socialist market economy in China , the sponsors noted .
The institute was sponsored by the State Commission for Restructuring the Economy , the China Research Institute for Restructuring the Economy and the China Systems Sciences Research Institute .
Li Tieying , member of Political Bureau of the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China ( CPC ) and State Councillor , and Wang Guangying , vice-chairman of the Standing Committee of the National People 's Congress , attended today 's opening ceremony .
Li , who is also minister in charge of the State Commission for Restructuring the Economy , and retired leader Bo Yibo are honorary presidents of the research institute .
Wu Jie , vice-minister of the State Commission for Restructuring the Economy , was elected president of the institute .
